<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-9576] Connection leak in CQLRecordWriter</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-9576</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Ran into connection leaks when using CQLCassandra apache-cassandra-2.2.0-beta1-src + CQLOutputFormat (via CqlNativeStorage). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems like the order blocks of code starting at &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/trunk/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/hadoop/cql3/CqlRecordWriter.java#L298&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/trunk/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/hadoop/cql3/CqlRecordWriter.java#L298&lt;/a&gt; were reversed in 2.2 which leads to the connection leaks.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
                <environment></environment>
